# Nomina — Design System & Responsiveness Rules

> **RULE #1 — This is the foundational rule for the entire project.**
> Every page, component, and layout MUST comply with these standards.

## Responsiveness (Mandatory)

- Every page MUST be fully responsive across **mobile** (320px+), **tablet** (768px+), and **desktop** (1280px+)
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`) — **never** hardcode desktop-only layouts
- Test at these breakpoints: `375px` (mobile), `768px` (tablet), `1440px` (desktop)
- Touch targets MUST be ≥ 44px on mobile
- Navigation must collapse to a hamburger or bottom nav on mobile
- Forms must stack vertically on mobile
- Grids: `grid-cols-1` base → `sm:grid-cols-2` → `lg:grid-cols-3` (or appropriate)

## Design Consistency (Mandatory)

- All pages MUST use the global color palette — **no ad-hoc hex, rgb, or hsl colors**
- Use CSS custom properties (`var(--token)`) or Tailwind theme extensions only
- Typography, spacing, border-radius, and shadow MUST follow the design tokens below
- Every interactive element (button, link, input, card) MUST have hover, focus, and active states
- Maintain consistent visual rhythm: same spacing, same card styles, same header patterns across all pages

